761
00:53:45,200 --> 00:53:46,200
I see dead people!

762
00:54:01,510 --> 00:54:02,860
Is it the ghost in your room?

763
00:54:15,600 --> 00:54:16,440
What are you even scared of?

764
00:54:16,540 --> 00:54:17,200
Here.

765
00:54:18,320 --> 00:54:19,640
Whoa, you!

766
00:54:20,280 --> 00:54:21,000
Whoa...

767
00:54:21,760 --> 00:54:23,000
My heart almost stopped beating.

768
00:54:25,040 --> 00:54:26,480
I'm so happy...

769
00:54:33,980 --> 00:54:35,560
I put a lot of thought into this.

770
00:54:38,800 --> 00:54:39,880
Thank you.

771
00:54:41,100 --> 00:54:42,800
You put a lot of thought into this for me?

772
00:54:49,020 --> 00:54:49,880
Let me see.

773
00:54:54,960 --> 00:54:56,080
Wow...

774
00:55:06,900 --> 00:55:08,280
Whoa, you!

775
00:55:08,660 --> 00:55:09,640
These are nice.

776
00:55:09,940 --> 00:55:10,960
I love them.

777
00:55:17,720 --> 00:55:19,080
But you shouldn't have.

778
00:55:19,800 --> 00:55:21,400
They're really expensive.

779
00:55:21,400 --> 00:55:22,840
Are you really gifting these to me?

780
00:55:23,820 --> 00:55:25,080
What about all the fuss about my camera?

781
00:55:25,800 --> 00:55:26,680
Mm.

782
00:55:26,840 --> 00:55:29,400
That's why I was debating
whether or not I should gift them to you.

783
00:55:30,160 --> 00:55:31,720
But after some pondering,

784
00:55:32,520 --> 00:55:33,960
since I genuinely
wanted to give them to you,

785
00:55:34,440 --> 00:55:35,560
I decided to buy them.

786
00:55:36,640 --> 00:55:38,200
Plus, I'm not struggling.

787
00:55:40,300 --> 00:55:41,520
I knew how expensive they were,

788
00:55:44,380 --> 00:55:45,640
but they just really suit you.

789
00:55:48,880 --> 00:55:50,040
I love you, Qin.

790
00:55:53,240 --> 00:55:54,280
I love you, too, Duang.

791
00:56:05,540 --> 00:56:06,880
Here you go.

792
00:56:08,080 --> 00:56:09,320
Thank you.

793
00:56:13,560 --> 00:56:17,320
[Today's mood is good;
my boyfriend picked my outfit]

794
00:56:26,720 --> 00:56:29,080
Is this a makeover or a renovation?

795
00:56:29,560 --> 00:56:31,010
Jettana,

796
00:56:31,040 --> 00:56:32,200
just say you're jelly.

797
00:56:35,660 --> 00:56:38,400
Who'd be jealous
of a lover boy showing off his love?

798
00:56:39,960 --> 00:56:41,770
When will it be your turn?

799
00:56:41,800 --> 00:56:43,800
Is hooking up
all you'll ever look for in life?

800
00:56:49,660 --> 00:56:51,080
Are you making your own clothes?

801
00:56:53,400 --> 00:56:54,800
It's for you.

802
00:56:55,600 --> 00:56:56,840
Try it on for me.

803
00:56:57,630 --> 00:56:59,080
What made you decide to tailor it for me?

804
00:57:00,680 --> 00:57:03,440
Well, maybe we've been together so much
I know the size you wear.

805
00:57:04,420 --> 00:57:06,720
- Hm...
- Get up.

806
00:57:11,800 --> 00:57:12,440
Here.

807
00:57:17,980 --> 00:57:19,520
Hold up...

808
00:57:20,760 --> 00:57:22,520
Go change it properly, not here.

809
00:57:23,120 --> 00:57:24,160
What?

810
00:57:24,460 --> 00:57:25,600
Why not?

811
00:57:25,820 --> 00:57:27,360
There's nothing you haven't seen, right?

812
00:57:31,280 --> 00:57:32,080
Alright, alright.

813
00:57:32,540 --> 00:57:33,880
I'll go change in the bathroom.

814
00:57:50,040 --> 00:57:51,520
Here I am.

815
00:57:53,900 --> 00:57:54,480
Mm,

816
00:57:55,400 --> 00:57:57,100
that looks sharp.
It really suits you.

817
00:58:04,560 --> 00:58:05,640
Try this one on for me.

818
00:58:09,840 --> 00:58:10,960
An overall?

819
00:58:17,920 --> 00:58:18,920
Please?

820
00:58:20,900 --> 00:58:22,680
Will it really look good on me?

821
00:58:23,740 --> 00:58:24,760
Of course.

822
00:58:24,980 --> 00:58:26,070
You have a good body.

823
00:58:26,100 --> 00:58:27,360
Anything looks good on you.

824
00:58:29,720 --> 00:58:31,960
I really like your eyes
when you get serious.

825
00:58:33,120 --> 00:58:34,320
Then...

826
00:58:35,400 --> 00:58:37,800
Would you be a model for my final project?

827
00:58:38,520 --> 00:58:40,240
If I agree to being your model,

828
00:58:40,780 --> 00:58:41,760
what would I get?

829
00:58:42,940 --> 00:58:44,440
Well, what do you want?

830
00:58:49,400 --> 00:58:51,720
You know too well what I want.

831
00:58:54,340 --> 00:58:56,760
Are you sure this is all you want?

832
00:59:18,960 --> 00:59:20,160
I want you more.

833
00:59:22,420 --> 00:59:23,440
I'm not falling in love.

834
00:59:24,320 --> 00:59:25,160
Marvis...

835
00:59:38,800 --> 00:59:39,440
Huh?

836
00:59:40,880 --> 00:59:42,160
You know I'm not good with words.

837
00:59:42,740 --> 00:59:44,480
Yes, I do.

838
00:59:45,660 --> 00:59:46,880
Would that be alright?

839
00:59:48,100 --> 00:59:49,560
It's completely fine.

840
00:59:50,260 --> 00:59:52,560
If you don't want to talk, I will.

841
00:59:57,080 --> 00:59:59,600
Everyone in my family is talkative.

842
01:00:00,400 --> 01:00:02,760
Dad and Mami
are even more talkative than I am.

843
01:00:02,960 --> 01:00:04,240
Don't you worry.

844
01:00:04,640 --> 01:00:06,600
I'll never leave your side.

845
01:00:07,020 --> 01:00:08,080
Besides,

846
01:00:08,520 --> 01:00:10,640
you're a lot better
at having conversations with me.

847
01:00:13,140 --> 01:00:13,880
Mm.

848
01:00:14,260 --> 01:00:15,140
Thank you.

849
01:00:17,720 --> 01:00:18,720
What for?

850
01:00:20,720 --> 01:00:21,850
Thank you...

851
01:00:21,880 --> 01:00:24,120
for making me a better version of myself.

852
01:00:27,800 --> 01:00:29,280
I also thank you

853
01:00:29,680 --> 01:00:31,680
for making me

854
01:00:31,710 --> 01:00:33,320
a better version of myself.

855
01:00:47,160 --> 01:00:47,760
Come on.

856
01:00:49,560 --> 01:00:51,400
I'll hold your hand through all of it!

857
01:00:56,860 --> 01:00:57,480
Hey,

858
01:00:57,620 --> 01:00:58,520
how am I gonna get out of the car?

859
01:00:58,580 --> 01:00:59,200
Oh...

860
01:01:04,530 --> 01:01:06,320
Did you transfer him the money?

861
01:01:06,680 --> 01:01:08,000
Darling, darling, darling!

862
01:01:08,340 --> 01:01:08,960
Duang's home!

863
01:01:09,020 --> 01:01:11,120
Jeez, like no one can tell
you miss your son.

864
01:01:11,540 --> 01:01:12,390
You...

865
01:01:12,420 --> 01:01:13,520
Oh, Duang!

866
01:01:14,380 --> 01:01:15,050
Duang, Duang!

867
01:01:15,080 --> 01:01:18,600
I'm home!

868
01:01:19,040 --> 01:01:20,110
Hello, Dad.

869
01:01:20,140 --> 01:01:21,270
- Hello, Mami.
- Hello.

870
01:01:21,300 --> 01:01:23,360
Hi, there. Come here, Duang.

871
01:01:24,080 --> 01:01:25,800
Give Mami a hug. Ooh, I miss you!

872
01:01:29,320 --> 01:01:30,200
Funan, hi.

873
01:01:30,420 --> 01:01:31,200
Hey.

874
01:01:32,900 --> 01:01:35,480
Look at your brother for once,
not just your phone!

875
01:01:35,960 --> 01:01:37,000
Bro, look over there.

876
01:01:37,140 --> 01:01:38,470
Look at Dad and Mami.

877
01:01:38,500 --> 01:01:39,760
They're missing you to death!

878
01:01:39,860 --> 01:01:42,200
It wouldn't feel right
if these two didn't fight.

879
01:01:42,300 --> 01:01:44,120
Stop right here, guys.

880
01:01:45,080 --> 01:01:46,560
I've brought someone special.

881
01:01:48,620 --> 01:01:49,400
This is Qin!

882
01:01:52,080 --> 01:01:52,920
Too soon!

883
01:01:53,790 --> 01:01:54,850
I'm just so excited!

884
01:01:54,880 --> 01:01:55,720
He's my boyfriend.

885
01:01:56,000 --> 01:01:56,840
He is...

886
01:01:59,920 --> 01:02:01,000
He's adorable.

887
01:02:02,560 --> 01:02:03,290
Qin...

888
01:02:03,320 --> 01:02:04,690
- Hello, Mom.
- Hi, sweetie.

889
01:02:04,720 --> 01:02:05,680
Hello, Dad.

890
01:02:06,180 --> 01:02:07,720
- Hello, Funan.
- Hi.

891
01:02:09,240 --> 01:02:09,800
Dad,

892
01:02:10,480 --> 01:02:11,960
Duang really did it!

893
01:02:12,320 --> 01:02:13,480
Right?

894
01:02:13,880 --> 01:02:15,770
I thought this day would never come.

895
01:02:15,800 --> 01:02:17,920
Hey, don't make fun of your child!

896
01:02:18,020 --> 01:02:19,920
Duang is my son.
Of course, he did it.

897
01:02:20,720 --> 01:02:22,560
Mami, you're buttering me up.

898
01:02:22,800 --> 01:02:24,610
But let me tell you guys that

899
01:02:24,640 --> 01:02:26,560
Qin isn't good with words.

900
01:02:26,590 --> 01:02:28,090
Please be patient with him.

901
01:02:28,120 --> 01:02:29,200
Oh, it's completely fine.

902
01:02:29,230 --> 01:02:30,800
Make yourself at home, Qin.

903
01:02:30,830 --> 01:02:32,570
Every animal you see has been vaccinated,

904
01:02:32,600 --> 01:02:34,440
so make yourself comfortable.

905
01:02:34,630 --> 01:02:35,440
We're not animals.

906
01:02:36,460 --> 01:02:37,240
Alright.

907
01:02:44,480 --> 01:02:45,440
Qin!

908
01:02:45,480 --> 01:02:47,480
My, my, you're so cute.

909
01:02:47,600 --> 01:02:48,890
What a cute one.

910
01:02:48,920 --> 01:02:50,410
You're really handsome, too.

911
01:02:50,440 --> 01:02:51,970
Exactly like what Duang described.

912
01:02:52,000 --> 01:02:53,370
True, Mami.

913
01:02:53,400 --> 01:02:56,400
He's the CEO of being adorable!

914
01:02:56,460 --> 01:02:57,880
Right, Qin, Qin, Qin.

915
01:02:58,860 --> 01:03:01,400
Have you ever tried Betong chicken?

916
01:03:02,100 --> 01:03:03,120
- Jeez, Dad.
- Why now?

917
01:03:03,480 --> 01:03:04,960
Is this how you're approaching
your son's boyfriend?

918
01:03:04,990 --> 01:03:05,930
Right? I'm also confused.

919
01:03:05,960 --> 01:03:06,840
Come on now.

920
01:03:06,980 --> 01:03:08,200
Uh...I haven't.

921
01:03:08,640 --> 01:03:09,930
But I have seen some pictures.

922
01:03:09,960 --> 01:03:11,880
Right, it's okay if you haven't.

923
01:03:11,940 --> 01:03:13,890
But is there something else you like?

924
01:03:13,920 --> 01:03:16,640
Duang said you have
many favorites, like desserts and all that.

925
01:03:16,670 --> 01:03:18,110
Yes, I like everything.

926
01:03:18,140 --> 01:03:19,010
Right.

927
01:03:19,040 --> 01:03:21,310
Would you like to come check them out
in the kitchen with me,

928
01:03:21,340 --> 01:03:23,110
or would you prefer waiting out here?

929
01:03:23,140 --> 01:03:24,290
I'll... Uh...

930
01:03:24,320 --> 01:03:25,440
- Uh...
- Ugh, Mami.

931
01:03:25,580 --> 01:03:26,920
You're luring him with food.

932
01:03:26,950 --> 01:03:29,160
I'm not. I've just prepared a lot of food,

933
01:03:29,190 --> 01:03:31,730
so I want him
to check it out in the kitchen.

934
01:03:31,760 --> 01:03:32,330
Wanna come with?

935
01:03:32,360 --> 01:03:33,720
Sure, Mami. I'm coming with you.

936
01:03:33,960 --> 01:03:36,090
Qin, is the dining room
and the kitchen the same thing?

937
01:03:36,120 --> 01:03:37,170
Mami's confused.

938
01:03:37,200 --> 01:03:38,650
But I do think they might be.

939
01:03:38,680 --> 01:03:40,040
Qin, walk with me.

940
01:03:41,420 --> 01:03:42,650
- Duang.
- Yes?

941
01:03:42,680 --> 01:03:44,130
Come help me set the table.

942
01:03:44,160 --> 01:03:45,400
Uh, what about Funan?

943
01:03:46,760 --> 01:03:47,400
Whoa,

944
01:03:47,640 --> 01:03:48,800
don't point your finger at me.

945
01:03:49,020 --> 01:03:50,480
Shoo, go help Dad.

946
01:03:50,520 --> 01:03:52,200
Stop it. Both of you, come on.

947
01:03:52,230 --> 01:03:53,810
Help each other,
so we can get it over with.

948
01:03:53,840 --> 01:03:55,080
Come on, I'm hungry.

949
01:03:57,520 --> 01:03:58,080
Whoa!

950
01:04:00,880 --> 01:04:01,720
Qin?

951
01:04:02,200 --> 01:04:02,610
Yes?

952
01:04:02,640 --> 01:04:04,780
What specific desserts do you like?

953
01:04:05,710 --> 01:04:07,270
Umm... Nothing specific.

954
01:04:07,800 --> 01:04:09,720
I love every dessert out there.

955
01:04:09,860 --> 01:04:11,390
Nice, you're not picky.

956
01:04:11,420 --> 01:04:13,650
This family doesn't even look at desserts.

957
01:04:13,680 --> 01:04:16,670
I even took some classes
at Mamon Gordon Bowwow

958
01:04:16,700 --> 01:04:18,840
and never got to show off my skills, Qin.

959
01:04:18,940 --> 01:04:20,400
What level of sweetness do you like?

960
01:04:20,800 --> 01:04:22,830
- Just the normal one.
- That's right.

961
01:04:22,860 --> 01:04:25,450
If you want something sweet,
you need to go all the way, right?

962
01:04:25,480 --> 01:04:26,000
Here.

963
01:04:26,060 --> 01:04:27,850
I'll teach you
how to make agar-agar jelly.

964
01:04:27,880 --> 01:04:29,730
How does that sound?
It's not hard at all.

965
01:04:29,760 --> 01:04:30,770
It'll only take a sec,

966
01:04:30,800 --> 01:04:32,590
maybe after three or four stories.

967
01:04:32,620 --> 01:04:33,600
- Okay...
- Here, we'll start by

968
01:04:33,630 --> 01:04:34,890
lighting the stove,

969
01:04:34,920 --> 01:04:37,130
then you place the pot on it.

970
01:04:37,160 --> 01:04:38,090
It's so simple.

971
01:04:38,120 --> 01:04:39,050
See?

972
01:04:39,080 --> 01:04:40,810
But you can chillax

973
01:04:40,840 --> 01:04:43,050
because if it's edible, we'll eat it.

974
01:04:43,080 --> 01:04:45,120
If not, we'll throw it away.

975
01:04:45,400 --> 01:04:46,960
I know who Duang takes after.

976
01:04:47,120 --> 01:04:47,950
Hm?

977
01:04:47,980 --> 01:04:48,980
Is it me?

978
01:04:49,280 --> 01:04:50,880
Then, I have some more beans to spill.
Wanna listen?

979
01:04:51,160 --> 01:04:51,970
Please do, Mami.

980
01:04:52,000 --> 01:04:53,680
Right! Let's take a seat.

981
01:04:55,220 --> 01:04:57,550
Story time, when Duang was little,

982
01:04:57,580 --> 01:04:59,330
when I took him places,

983
01:04:59,360 --> 01:05:01,170
everyone said
we were like two peas in a pod.

984
01:05:02,320 --> 01:05:02,880
Ow...

985
01:05:04,320 --> 01:05:05,360
What are you sneaking on?

986
01:05:07,320 --> 01:05:09,200
Right...

987
01:05:09,400 --> 01:05:10,970
On your boyfriend

988
01:05:11,000 --> 01:05:12,640
to see if he gets along well with Mami?

989
01:05:13,160 --> 01:05:15,360
Aw, you puppy!

990
01:05:15,620 --> 01:05:16,760
I'm so happy

991
01:05:17,520 --> 01:05:19,480
that Qin gets along with our family.

992
01:05:23,860 --> 01:05:24,570
Funan,

993
01:05:24,600 --> 01:05:25,860
- Hm?
- I have a question.

994
01:05:26,600 --> 01:05:27,280
What?

995
01:05:28,700 --> 01:05:29,700
Do you think...

996
01:05:29,980 --> 01:05:31,960
Dad and Mami are okay with Qin?

997
01:05:32,740 --> 01:05:33,740
Look at them.

998
01:05:34,580 --> 01:05:36,090
That's the look of someone not being okay?

999
01:05:36,120 --> 01:05:37,890
Qin, you sing so beautifully!

1000
01:05:37,920 --> 01:05:39,320
Have you taken
vocal classes since childhood?

1001
01:05:39,420 --> 01:05:41,200
Mami is kind.

1002
01:05:41,340 --> 01:05:42,390
As for Dad,

1003
01:05:42,420 --> 01:05:43,420
even though he's a poser,

1004
01:05:43,800 --> 01:05:45,200
he's also nice.

1005
01:05:45,520 --> 01:05:46,770
- I'm snitching on your ass.
- Whoa!

1006
01:05:47,840 --> 01:05:48,840
Why did you ask?

1007
01:05:50,980 --> 01:05:52,640
I'm just scared
Qin would be uncomfortable.

1008
01:05:53,160 --> 01:05:55,120
Our family isn't like his.

1009
01:05:55,740 --> 01:05:57,080
Before you overthink,

1010
01:05:57,420 --> 01:05:58,560
have you asked him

1011
01:05:58,740 --> 01:06:00,000
if he's uncomfortable?

1012
01:06:01,840 --> 01:06:02,600
That's right,

1013
01:06:02,960 --> 01:06:04,640
so don't think for him.

1014
01:06:04,740 --> 01:06:05,890
Being in a relationship,

1015
01:06:05,920 --> 01:06:07,440
you can't think for each other.

1016
01:06:07,940 --> 01:06:09,120
You need to talk.

1017
01:06:10,160 --> 01:06:11,560
I'm scared he wouldn't like it.

1018
01:06:11,720 --> 01:06:12,810
Jeez,

1019
01:06:12,840 --> 01:06:14,050
if he doesn't,

1020
01:06:14,080 --> 01:06:15,320
he should tell you

1021
01:06:15,680 --> 01:06:18,720
because that means
you have to adapt to each other.

1022
01:06:18,840 --> 01:06:21,200
Even family members
can't think for each other.

1023
01:06:21,900 --> 01:06:22,750
So...

1024
01:06:22,780 --> 01:06:24,450
you need to have conversations

1025
01:06:24,480 --> 01:06:25,920
so that you know exactly
what each other thinks,

1026
01:06:27,040 --> 01:06:28,400
especially in a relationship

1027
01:06:28,720 --> 01:06:31,040
where you usually
grow up in a different environment.

1028
01:06:31,780 --> 01:06:33,400
Do you think what you're thinking for him

1029
01:06:33,820 --> 01:06:34,880
is accurate?

1030
01:06:36,940 --> 01:06:38,280
See? No freaking way it is.

1031
01:06:39,360 --> 01:06:40,360
Listen and think.

1032
01:06:40,760 --> 01:06:41,760
What comes after thinking?

1033
01:06:42,320 --> 01:06:43,520
Think, think, think.

1034
01:06:44,000 --> 01:06:46,360
Think and execute!

1035
01:06:49,160 --> 01:06:51,280
Let's go back to food for a bit.

1036
01:06:51,310 --> 01:06:53,320
What about savory dishes?
What do you like?

1037
01:06:53,720 --> 01:06:56,600
If it's something I have often,
it's maybe stir-fried shrimp with garlic.

1038
01:06:56,720 --> 01:06:57,400
Ooh,

1039
01:06:57,960 --> 01:06:59,490
do you know that Duang

1040
01:06:59,520 --> 01:07:01,720
asked me to teach him how to make that?

1041
01:07:01,880 --> 01:07:03,250
It took Dad and Funan

1042
01:07:03,280 --> 01:07:05,480
a week of shrimp before he got it.

1043
01:07:05,720 --> 01:07:06,950
So, did you get to taste it?

1044
01:07:06,980 --> 01:07:07,800
Was it any good?

1045
01:07:08,480 --> 01:07:09,700
I did. It was pretty good.

1046
01:07:09,820 --> 01:07:11,800
Mm, that's nice to hear.

1047
01:07:12,160 --> 01:07:15,320
But do you know that
Duang have many talents?

1048
01:07:15,580 --> 01:07:17,230
I sent him to every class out there.

1049
01:07:17,260 --> 01:07:19,690
Whatever he wanted to attend, I did.

1050
01:07:19,720 --> 01:07:21,730
Like when Duang
asked to take guitar classes,

1051
01:07:21,760 --> 01:07:22,920
I allowed him to.

1052
01:07:23,020 --> 01:07:25,040
But after a while,
he said it hurt his hands.

1053
01:07:25,220 --> 01:07:25,930
So what did he do?

1054
01:07:25,960 --> 01:07:26,770
He had to quit

1055
01:07:26,800 --> 01:07:28,150
since it hurt, right?

1056
01:07:28,180 --> 01:07:30,400
After that, he was picked on,

1057
01:07:30,620 --> 01:07:31,920
so he wanted to take taekwondo classes.

1058
01:07:32,100 --> 01:07:33,830
I bought him the uniform

1059
01:07:33,860 --> 01:07:34,990
and got him geared up.

1060
01:07:35,020 --> 01:07:36,320
I got him all the belts out there.

1061
01:07:36,580 --> 01:07:38,450
Then he was kicked and hurt,

1062
01:07:38,480 --> 01:07:39,400
so there goes another class.

1063
01:07:39,960 --> 01:07:41,200
But I didn't give up.

1064
01:07:41,480 --> 01:07:44,080
After a while, he asked me
to join drawing classes.

1065
01:07:44,240 --> 01:07:45,520
That was when I felt a knot in my stomach

1066
01:07:45,660 --> 01:07:48,050
since it was an activity that required him
to concentrate and stay still.

1067
01:07:48,080 --> 01:07:50,080
I thought, "Gosh, he's not gonna last."

1068
01:07:50,110 --> 01:07:51,960
But in the end, he did!

1069
01:07:52,140 --> 01:07:53,840
I was over the moon, Qin.

1070
01:07:54,000 --> 01:07:55,800
This is what's right for him.

1071
01:07:57,740 --> 01:07:59,960
And so are you, I believe.

1072
01:08:02,440 --> 01:08:04,200
He really tried,

1073
01:08:04,820 --> 01:08:07,240
whether it's the show or the cooking.

1074
01:08:12,440 --> 01:08:13,920
From the eyes of a mother, right?

1075
01:08:16,640 --> 01:08:18,439
But I thank you

1076
01:08:19,420 --> 01:08:20,960
for being in his life.

1077
01:08:22,200 --> 01:08:23,600
There's no need to thank me, Mom.

1078
01:08:23,899 --> 01:08:25,600
You've raised him well.

1079
01:08:26,180 --> 01:08:28,120
That's why he turns out to be so lovable.

1080
01:08:29,640 --> 01:08:30,560
Besides,

1081
01:08:32,660 --> 01:08:34,000
I didn't choose him.

1082
01:08:34,340 --> 01:08:35,680
He chose me.

1083
01:08:41,240 --> 01:08:42,439
I understand

1084
01:08:42,750 --> 01:08:44,040
why it has to be you, Qin.

1085
01:08:49,420 --> 01:08:50,080
Jeez,

1086
01:08:50,640 --> 01:08:52,210
my voice is starting to get shaky.

1087
01:08:52,240 --> 01:08:54,600
Let's light up the stove
and make agar-agar jelly, Qin.

1088
01:09:00,800 --> 01:09:01,399
Here.

1089
01:09:01,760 --> 01:09:02,720
This is yours.

1090
01:09:03,479 --> 01:09:05,000
Betong chicken.

1091
01:09:07,439 --> 01:09:08,160
Qin.

1092
01:09:08,520 --> 01:09:09,240
Yes?

1093
01:09:09,720 --> 01:09:11,080
Eat tons.

1094
01:09:11,380 --> 01:09:13,640
Mami's Betong chicken

1095
01:09:13,859 --> 01:09:15,560
is the best in the entire world.

1096
01:09:15,620 --> 01:09:17,410
That's right. I worked so hard on it.

1097
01:09:17,439 --> 01:09:19,290
The meat is gonna be so tender.

1098
01:09:19,319 --> 01:09:20,479
Okay.

1099
01:09:20,620 --> 01:09:21,240
Mm-hm.

1100
01:09:23,319 --> 01:09:24,140
Quiet down!

1101
01:09:24,319 --> 01:09:25,120
It's embarrassing to the guest!

1102
01:09:26,939 --> 01:09:27,649
Hey.

1103
01:09:27,680 --> 01:09:28,319
Hm?

1104
01:09:29,399 --> 01:09:30,680
Do you want to spend the night here?

1105
01:09:32,680 --> 01:09:33,359
Spend the night?

1106
01:09:43,520 --> 01:09:45,200
Since you drove a long way,

1107
01:09:45,420 --> 01:09:47,080
just spend the night here, alright?

1108
01:09:47,600 --> 01:09:48,640
True.

1109
01:09:48,939 --> 01:09:49,920
- Honey!
- Hm?

1110
01:09:51,140 --> 01:09:52,439
Oh, that's right.

1111
01:09:52,640 --> 01:09:53,319
Uh...

1112
01:09:53,840 --> 01:09:54,840
Tonight,

1113
01:09:55,240 --> 01:09:56,800
stay over, would you?

1114
01:09:57,780 --> 01:09:58,650
Uh...

1115
01:09:58,680 --> 01:10:00,170
Just stay the night.

1116
01:10:00,200 --> 01:10:02,080
I have so much to gossip about.

1117
01:10:02,300 --> 01:10:04,330
Also, I've received
a notification from the TMD

1118
01:10:04,360 --> 01:10:06,170
that it's going to rain cats and dogs.

1119
01:10:06,200 --> 01:10:07,920
I'll be worried
if you make another trip back!

1120
01:10:08,200 --> 01:10:09,730
- No...
- Whoa, really?!

1121
01:10:09,760 --> 01:10:12,800
- That's dangerous.
- Couldn't be more dangerous, Mami!

1122
01:10:13,080 --> 01:10:14,810
No, that's dangerous.

1123
01:10:14,840 --> 01:10:15,880
Seriously!

1124
01:10:18,440 --> 01:10:19,440
- Or maybe you can spend half the night.
- Yeah.

1125
01:10:19,540 --> 01:10:20,440
Let's eat first.

1126
01:10:21,000 --> 01:10:21,720
Please stay over.

1127
01:10:22,600 --> 01:10:23,240
Alright, thank you.

1128
01:10:23,440 --> 01:10:24,160
Yes.

1129
01:10:25,680 --> 01:10:27,290
Right? It's gonna be a dangerous ride.

1130
01:10:27,320 --> 01:10:29,210
What if there's an accident?

1131
01:10:29,240 --> 01:10:30,570
Yeah, it's better this way.

1132
01:10:30,600 --> 01:10:32,330
We wouldn't have to be anxious.

1133
01:10:32,360 --> 01:10:32,760
Exactly.

1134
01:10:32,860 --> 01:10:33,480
So...

1135
01:10:33,890 --> 01:10:35,360
Do you have classes tomorrow?

1136
01:10:36,120 --> 01:10:36,960
I do...

1137
01:10:39,320 --> 01:10:40,000
In the afternoon.

1138
01:10:42,440 --> 01:10:43,680
I also have an afternoon class.

1139
01:10:44,340 --> 01:10:45,850
Then, how about
you go back tomorrow morning?

1140
01:10:47,540 --> 01:10:48,890
Yes, tomorrow morning.

1141
01:10:48,920 --> 01:10:51,440
So, Qin will be in Duang's room, then.

1142
01:10:52,520 --> 01:10:53,240
What?!

1143
01:10:53,300 --> 01:10:54,760
Of course, he will!

1144
01:10:55,060 --> 01:10:55,640
What?

1145
01:10:55,880 --> 01:10:57,770
Why are you screaming at me?

1146
01:10:57,800 --> 01:10:59,730
Of course, Qin will be in your room.

1147
01:10:59,760 --> 01:11:01,560
How could he be in mine?

1148
01:11:01,640 --> 01:11:03,410
Why would he be in your room?!

1149
01:11:03,440 --> 01:11:04,800
He won't!

1150
01:11:04,860 --> 01:11:06,920
He will be in your room!

1151
01:11:07,320 --> 01:11:09,370
Do you have to keep raising your voice?

1152
01:11:09,400 --> 01:11:10,610
He will be in your room, of course.

1153
01:11:10,640 --> 01:11:12,440
I've already cleaned it!

1154
01:11:12,500 --> 01:11:15,130
Alright, alright, let me put it to bed.

1155
01:11:15,840 --> 01:11:17,090
Qin,

1156
01:11:17,240 --> 01:11:18,640
you'll sleep in Duang's room.

1157
01:11:18,820 --> 01:11:19,170
End of story.

1158
01:11:19,200 --> 01:11:20,400
- Yeah, that's all there is.
- Alright.

1159
01:11:34,360 --> 01:11:35,920
It's a hundred times
cleaner than your condo.

1160
01:11:37,360 --> 01:11:38,360
Definitely.

1161
01:11:39,060 --> 01:11:41,360
Mami is very hygienic.

1162
01:11:42,340 --> 01:11:44,040
I can tell. Your house is neat.

1163
01:11:59,780 --> 01:12:01,680
This was from
when I took taekwondo classes.

1164
01:12:02,260 --> 01:12:03,600
It lasted three days before I quit.

1165
01:12:04,980 --> 01:12:06,120
Your mom already spilled everything.

1166
01:12:06,780 --> 01:12:07,520
Whoa,

1167
01:12:08,440 --> 01:12:10,640
she gossiped about me?

1168
01:12:10,900 --> 01:12:11,480
Mm.

1169
01:12:11,960 --> 01:12:12,880
But I do want to know more.

1170
01:12:13,180 --> 01:12:14,040
Tell me the story.

1171
01:12:14,780 --> 01:12:16,000
When I was small,

1172
01:12:16,000 --> 01:12:18,080
Mami had me do a lot of things,

1173
01:12:18,180 --> 01:12:20,280
but I was never good at anything.

1174
01:12:20,280 --> 01:12:21,200
Luckily,

1175
01:12:21,200 --> 01:12:23,680
she told me to tell her
if I didn't come to like it.

1176
01:12:24,620 --> 01:12:26,080
Mami said,

1177
01:12:26,500 --> 01:12:29,120
"Don't be afraid to fail

1178
01:12:29,300 --> 01:12:31,080
if you're eager to get back on your feet."

1179
01:12:32,060 --> 01:12:33,240
She's such an angel.

1180
01:12:33,460 --> 01:12:34,640
I really like your family.

1181
01:12:35,140 --> 01:12:36,920
That's how I found out

1182
01:12:37,520 --> 01:12:39,280
I like drawing the most.

1183
01:12:39,720 --> 01:12:40,600
But now,

1184
01:12:41,720 --> 01:12:43,880
I like you even more!

1185
01:12:55,680 --> 01:12:56,440
Stop it.

1186
01:12:59,760 --> 01:13:00,440
Duang!

1187
01:13:08,780 --> 01:13:10,080
Hey, that's a cute picture.

1188
01:13:11,280 --> 01:13:12,120
Gee,

1189
01:13:12,720 --> 01:13:14,960
why don't we take a shower together
if you're gonna compliment me this much?

1190
01:13:15,460 --> 01:13:16,320
What a danger.

1191
01:13:16,840 --> 01:13:17,880
Are you crazy?

1192
01:13:17,940 --> 01:13:19,720
I won't do it
unless you allow me to.

1193
01:13:20,100 --> 01:13:20,840
Wow,

1194
01:13:20,980 --> 01:13:22,520
I didn't tell you to slide
your hand under, yet you did.

1195
01:13:22,520 --> 01:13:23,680
That's nuts!

1196
01:13:31,420 --> 01:13:32,000
Here.

1197
01:13:32,260 --> 01:13:33,400
This is your PJs.

1198
01:13:33,460 --> 01:13:34,820
No need for underwear.

1199
01:13:34,820 --> 01:13:36,280
I'll get your clothes all washed up.

1200
01:13:38,420 --> 01:13:39,600
Another nasty fucking thought.

1201
01:13:39,820 --> 01:13:41,040
You brought it up.

1202
01:13:41,300 --> 01:13:42,600
I was just mentioning it.

1203
01:13:43,660 --> 01:13:44,760
Let's take a shower together.

1204
01:13:45,580 --> 01:13:46,800
Save the environment.

1205
01:13:50,240 --> 01:13:51,080
Caving in?

1206
01:13:52,120 --> 01:13:53,240
Or do I need to pull a leg hug?

1207
01:13:57,620 --> 01:13:59,800
If you want me to,
we're going straight to sleep after that.

1208
01:14:00,060 --> 01:14:01,400
No more being all over me.

1209
01:14:02,400 --> 01:14:03,200
You got it.

1210
01:14:11,360 --> 01:14:12,800
Get me a towel.

1211
01:14:12,820 --> 01:14:13,600
I don't have one.

1212
01:15:18,340 --> 01:15:19,360
You're all mine.

1213
01:16:00,780 --> 01:16:01,480
Duang...

1214
01:16:02,000 --> 01:16:02,840
Don't bite.

1215
01:16:14,300 --> 01:16:15,160
Just a little taste.

1216
01:16:30,340 --> 01:16:32,340
I can't endure it anymore.

1217
01:16:35,660 --> 01:16:36,840
You're just...

1218
01:16:37,180 --> 01:16:38,180
Please?

1219
01:17:43,690 --> 01:17:45,540
Even though it's a little confusing
that we had to come to Japan,

1220
01:17:45,580 --> 01:17:48,440
- I think the timing is just perfect.
- What do you mean?

1221
01:17:48,590 --> 01:17:51,090
Perfect for our honeymoon trip, of course.

1222
01:17:52,900 --> 01:17:54,630
Today is our monthiversary.

1223
01:17:54,700 --> 01:17:56,530
I want this trip to be a gift for you.

1224
01:17:56,560 --> 01:17:57,920
What's the difference between

1225
01:17:58,260 --> 01:17:59,640
being into someone
and liking them?

1226
01:17:59,680 --> 01:18:01,150
Uh, excuse me.

1227
01:18:01,520 --> 01:18:04,060
I wanna sing the song I wrote for Duang.

1228
01:18:04,240 --> 01:18:05,290
Duang,

1229
01:18:06,190 --> 01:18:07,570
I wrote this song for you.

1230
01:18:07,900 --> 01:18:10,780
♫I'm lucky to have you here♫

1231
01:18:10,830 --> 01:18:18,320
♫Even if today your dreams long to bloom,♫

1232
01:18:18,720 --> 01:18:24,290
♫Be kind to yourself tonight♫

1233
01:18:24,990 --> 01:18:33,200
♫As long as you believe
that your hope stays close to you,♫

1234
01:18:33,740 --> 01:18:39,970
♫Beautiful days come with time♫

1235
01:18:41,730 --> 01:18:47,000
♫Just smiling back at yourself and falling rain♫

1236
01:18:47,040 --> 01:18:52,140
♫Better days are waiting,♫

1237
01:18:52,320 --> 01:19:00,250
♫Happiness will find you♫

1238
01:19:06,730 --> 01:19:10,240
[Duang With You]

